# Frontend (React / Next.js)

- Use TypeScript wherever possible
- Prefer functional components and React Hooks
- Follow existing state management in the codebase (Context, Redux Toolkit, etc.)
- Build reusable components per atomic design layers
- Ensure responsive design and accessibility
- Avoid unnecessary re-renders; optimize when it matters
- Use memoization only when it provides measurable value

## Error handling

- Handle loading, empty, and error states
- Add meaningful error messages
- Fail gracefully — never crash the UI silently

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — explicit UI states
if (isLoading) return <Spinner />;
if (error) return <ErrorMessage message={error.message} />;
if (!data?.length) return <EmptyState />;
```
